The paper involves the use of deep learning models for the analysis of histopathologic slide images of cervix squamous carcinoma. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and random forest for feature extraction and classification respectively, also falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of image retrieval techniques for location identification, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
